caption: Excellent eclectic twist on pasta with wonderful wine pairings. Service was so friendly.
Loved this place! The chicken and dumplings,  carbonate, and paparadelle were great. Can't wait to come back.
The food is amazing specially the winter squash salad. The place is clean and nice. I want to try the backyard patio next time I visit this majestic place.

I'm not normally one to write a review but the experience at Daisies was too wonderful to not share. First of all, Yasmin killed it- best server hands down (sorry everyone else). Secondly, the food was amazing. We were here to celebrate my birthday and my mother (who does not like pasta) loved the experience & food. She was still talking about it today! We practically ordered the whole menu & shared everything and I can't say there was something I didn't like. It's also very hard to pick a favorite! I will add that every person we had an interaction with was very nice & the staff in general takes Covid seriously. If you're worried about leaving your home to go into to a restaurant, don't be- go here.

Why does any restaurant use a third party vendor to take orders for them on line? And especially for pickup???!!! And specifically why does Daisies use Tock? We love Daisies and would love for them to not just survive but thrive! Today we discovered that you cannot use a Daisies gift card when placing an order at Daisies on Tock! No problem, just call them up and place your order over the phone, right? Nope..... you can't do that. You can only place an order for them on Tock! For those who would still like to use your gift card for a pick up order, here is how you have to do it. Call them up..... Explain what you want to the person who works there, at the restaurant, who can't take your order!  Read them the 16 digit number from your gift card to them over the phone. They will write it down or type it into their system (the note pad or system they used to use when they could take your order over the phone). Then go on line and place your order on Tock! They have promised me that when my order comes up on their system, the one they used to be able to take your order over the phone on, they will apply your gift card. Would somebody please explain to me how, why this is better? At least, I assume Tock is paying Daisies for complicating on line order taking, forcing Daisies from taking orders over the phone, and irritating their customers, right? (Fat chance!)  Second question. (Rhetorical),  Now that I have used Tock once, because I had no other option if I wanted to order from Daisies, how do I get Tock to stop bombarding me with junk email!?  Third Question. define Kafkaesque?

In terms of their food, every dish was excellent and I love the fact that they source locally where they can. Our table started with the Onion Dip, Herb Salad and Cauliflower. The flavors in all three were amazing. I am gluten sensitive and they import GF pasta from Italy. The Gnocchi dish was great. The Chitarra was out of this world and I highly recommend.
Amazing pasta. Great creative dishes

This is one of my favorite restaurants in Chicago. I was lucky enough to have a lovely dining experience on their backyard patio. The restaurant has an excellent selection of wines and fantastic food. The winter squash salad with brown butter was mouthwatering and a dish to die for. Also, their pasta is dangerously delicious: I always want to order another pasta dish. I am looking forward to going back to this place. And they employed cats.
love the food
They did a wonderful takeout Thanksgiving meal. All the dishes were easy to reheat and everything was super tasty. Highly recommend! Very excited to dine in once its safe

The ambiance is cozy and we went in on-peak hours but we were seated immediately. The staff was friendly and prompt. They proactively offer refills. The side dishes were yum and plateful and the egg were delicious. Servings were appropriate and service was quick. We would definitely go back!

Beware of their overpriced price gauging and extremely small portions. The best example is their Thanksgiving offer: “Customers can purchase a la carte dishes in store or order a $240 dinner for four. For those who’d rather cook, the meal is available as a $180 reheatable kit.” The owner, who has a bad reputation around Logan, wants to charge $60 during a recession to reheat your food for you. Lol.

Unfortunately had issues with the website but was able to order via Caviar (where the menu is limited). You can also order by phone from 10am if you have issues.  Did the (limited) lunchbox deal - the wagyu sandwich was delicious and the lunchbox is a nice touch.

Extremely unprofessional head chef/owner, I love supporting Logan Square farm to table restaurants but I cannot support a restaurant that retaliates against customers giving constructive feedback with rude pretentiousness. Go to Lula Café or Osteria Langhe nearby for the same quality & same culinary (decades-old) concept with even better food.  Sort by lowest reviews first to see I am not alone in my poor feedback and service experience. You’ll even see a rude comment reply from an owner. Disgraceful that they state they simply don’t care about poor experiences with such inflated pricey small portions. Read: greed.

1st time with takeout for lunch.  The sandwiches are great!  Had the chicken parm and sweet potato panini and potato salad on the side.  My only comment about the chicky chicky parm parm is that tomato flavor is less than one would expect compared to a "traditional", but the kale adds a welcomed acidity.
All the food is such high quality and taste. During the lockdown the sandwiches have become a new favorite!
Long wait for a small order with no customers.
Unique craft cocktails and friendly staff.

A great hidden gem, and definitely worth a visit!! The dishes utilize farm fresh ingredients, and handmade pastas. Highly recommend Stracci, Ravoli, pappardelle, and the Winter Squash Salad! And no.. you can never order too much!😋
Everything is delicious and fresh. Love the ISC sparkling!
Great food and service. The winter squash salad and tortellini were fantastic!
Great food, amazing server and we sat out on the patio, which was a great atmosphere. Even though we were observing Covid restrictions, it was a very enjoyable meal.

The staff was very accommodating, got me in without a reservation. As I walked into the place I though it was a little pretentious. The server was nice and recommended that I ordered 3 entries per person, which I thought was a bit much. I ordered the Overpriced Tomato to start. It stated that it had bone marrow but I didn't find it anywhere on my dish. However the tomatoes were super fresh, and the bread was out of this world. I would go back to try more.
Casual setting, elegant complex food! Such a special place. The service is excellent and the back patio is lovely and quiet.
If restaurants could be a soulmate, this would be mine.
Fabulous food, so many incredible flavors!!!  Great service, Nicole!

One of our new favorite spots! We were walking by and saw a sign to join them on the patio. From the front it just looks like a little cafe, but we knew there had to be more. Turns out...this place has amazing, home made food and quality service in a very relaxing and chill environment. They also have a small take out menu for fresh products. It's pretty brilliant, really. It allows the chef to continuously have fresh items without as much waste. The hostess was sweet...told us there weren't any tables outside, but she had the (open air) window table available. Since we can get kind of loud, it was a perfect locationfor us... out of the way with a cool breeze and a view. Our server Nicole made the experience for us though. She was friendly, witty, professional, funny and had a playful nature. She chose our food for us and we couldn't have been happier. The cocktails were thoughtfully prepared and not pretentious. The pastas were incredible and the desserts were just what they needed to be. I truly cant wait to go back. Thank you Nicole 💛
Very good pasta and drinks
Delicious pastas - but what blew me away the most were the amazing wines from the Midwest!
Delicious pasta, great wine, even better service!

Came here for our anniversary. Folk were full of beans and helpful. Nice casual good service. Pasta and a few other things, great cocktails. Filling! Intriguing hip part of town. Reminds me of Bristol.
It's rare to have a meal so perfectly excellent as this. If at all possible, go and eat here.

This place has great food and a lovely staff— attentive and so kind!!! I absolutely love the farm to table concept. Fresh ingredients and a menu that changes with the seasons. I can’t wait to see what they come up with in the summer.  Portions were on the smaller side, however our waiter (Seth, great guy) suggested we do one appetizer and entree per person. Pasta is filling, so either way I think it works out.  Great restaurant to enjoy a special occasion and indulge in the goodness!

In a word: mediocre. I’m not sure what exactly went wrong, service was good and the menu/reviews all seemed solid.  Every dish on the tasting menu just missed for us, nothing was bad but nothing was good either. The restaurant was very cramped but did not feel romantic or intimate.
very good food, great service, nice decor, vegan food options, great nonalcoholic drink options, fresh pasta

Funky spot. Interesting menu. Unique drinks. Potatoe wedges, meh, not bad, nothing special. Pastas, delicious. We tried the carbonara and tagliatelle. One dish came out cold, but they were extremely nice about it and quickly replaced it with a fresh dish. For dessert, blueberry pancakes. Very much homemade and wonderful. Try the beet old fashioned. I was skeptical, but was pleasantly satisfied. Great service. Enjoy!
Fantastic meal, yummy cocktails, friendly and courteous and knowledgeable wait staff! I highly recommend this place.
A new spot. Very quite a quiet intimate setting good for lunch meetings. An awesome desserts!
We had reservations for 5. Decided to share 8 plates. Some dishes were excellent gnocchi, tagliatelle, tortellini others were just ok. Service was friendly.
Unbelievably great service, food, and drinks. Great and plentiful vegetarian options. Our new favorite restaurant in Chicago by far. Amazing, get there now!
Great service. Great food!

Everything about our meal was fantastic. I always say that when I go out to dinner, I want a meal that I could never recreate at home. This meal is something I could never recreate. Fantastic meal and fantastic experience.
Incredible food, the tasting menu was diverse and filling. Loved the chip appetizer and all the pastas were diverse, colorful, and tasty. Always enjoy Daisies!

Undoubtedly top 5 restaurant in Chicago! Last night was my third time there and every time I am speechless by how great it is from start to finish. Service is amazing. The vibe in the space is friendly, cute, welcoming. All the appetizers are great. Love the cheese curds and OBSESSED with the winter squash salad. I could eat it everyday. We had 5 of the pastas and they were all so good. My favorite pasta was the truffle ravioli! We always recommend this place to our friends, and everyone who has been thinks it is a five star place!

Food and drink were excellent but everything had at least one ingredient that was super odd. I wanted a plain Old Fashioned drink without beets in it. They charged me an additional $6 on top of the regular drink charge and they said it was for ‘ bitters and simple syrup’. Well, what Old Fashioned does not have bitters and simple syrup????
Love this place
A very good dining experience. They were able to accommodate the vegan in our party. Service was very good. Some excellent pasta dishes.
The best food I've had in Chicago
Excellent, but need to watch the salt.
This is a great restaurant. We've been here a few times now and have never been disappointed. The food is amazing and their drinks are superb.  Everything was wonderful!!
Good food but small for the pasta portions.  Overpriced tomato was actually executed well for its price point with the bone marrow.
(Translated by Google) Delicious  (Original) Delicioso
Yummmsss get the lamb

What an awesome place! We came here craving for a carbonara that we had seen online, but we were informed it was no longer available. This did not disappoint us at all. Their new fall pastas certainly exceeded our expectations! The chitarra with tomato ragu and fresh basil and the gnocchi with wild mushroom and corn were both delicious! Definitely worth coming back for more.

Love pasta dishes, but a little tired of the usual standbys? Check out this place. All homemade pastas, reasonably priced and good portion sizes for sharing. All the pasta toppings are originals using seasonal ingredients. We also liked the interesting latke appetizer, but afterwards realized we couldn’t taste any whitefish in it. Maybe they forgot it? Lastly, the wine list is interesting and also decently priced. Excellent advice from the sommelier.

Overall, delicious food! All hand made to order pasta. The portion sizes are very small for the price you pay. Consider it a once or twice a year date place. Had their hand crafted root beer; a very unique flavor profile that you won’t forget!
Incredible food, Excellent service. Best carbonara I've had in a long time.
Please please please have the pasta

The staff was wonderful and very attentive and I loved the atmosphere. We had a couple different cocktails, one of which was a gin based herbal and earthy drink that was really good. The overpriced tomato appetizer was in fact, overpriced for the portions served, but was good. We also had their trout special and a couple pasta dishes. I had a vegetarian pasta dish with the gluten free pasta and it ended up being $24 for what was a very small portion, yet still very good. Considering the simplicity and portion sizes of the dishes, the prices are too high. I do applaud them for having a lot of gluten free options, but the $5 upcharge for gluten free pasta seems high to me.
Excellent farm to table spot with homemade pastas.  Great menu, great food.
Fun wine list
Bad management. I’ll never eat here again.  Edit: I only have 7 views on my comment including yours. You obviously care lol

25 dollars for 6 small ravioli is not an entree. Before you read further feel free to check out my other reviews, they are almost universally positive. I don't just go around complaining.  This place takes advantage of its customers once they are in the door. Online it says entrees are 15-25 dollars. Our waitress suggested that we order 2 appetizers and 5 entrees between two of us!  The definition of 'entree' is "the main course of the meal". Suggesting that two regular people need 5 main courses between them means that this place is gaming the system and redefining words to suit their needs to get people in the door.  I feel bad for the couple on their first date who were next to us, ordered drinks, an appetizer, and two entrees, and we heard comment that it looked like they still needed to go elsewhere for the rest of their dinner.  The food was really good, and if their menu said "small bites" or something along those lines instead of the grossly misleading "entrees" I would have given 5 stars. It's really predatory to get people in the door and then explain the liberties you have taken with the English language. People with friends or on first dates are now embarrassed to not want to spend 2.5x what they would at a restaurant that is not misleading them, so they stay. Solid business plan.
Terrific everything. Dishes are amazing and creative. Would recommend the tasting menu and any of the cocktails
Awesome food and service.   Highly recommended. Loved all the hand made pastas!  Appetizers were also delicious!
Had the mushroom risotto, it was creamy and full of flavor. Tiramisu was rich and decadent. It looked so good I forgot to take pictures, because I wanted to try it. Service was great.
Great food and drink, friendly staff with great menu recommendations!
Very very very good food.  Locally sourced fresh fruits vegetables and herbs. Very light on meat on the menu but they make up for it with taste. Worth a stop

The food was hit and miss. I got a quail dish which was exceedingly delicious as well as well rounded with the added additions of a purée and vegetable, but not a regular menu item. Everyone else at our table got a pasta dish from their menu. I think the problem was price point v. portion and distinction. All the pasta dishes were good, but not great and at that price point you expect great. Also the portions were exceedingly small and not meant to fill up even a small person like myself. There aren’t any sides to choose from....no bread or salad or vegetable options and they need to seriously revamp their appetizer selection. The patio is lovely but for what you get v. what you pay there are much better options as in Duck Inn, Tanta and Monnie Burke’s.
The gnocchi was the best ever. Absolutely loved the mushrooms and cheese curds. All dishes can be made vegetarian friendly.

I’m not usually one to bash a restaurant. But that being said after posting my review on yelp I was contacted by a extremely classless rude manager. His excuse for not having air conditioning on a 88 degree day was that it was an old building🙄. Except they had the doors wide open all evening.  Then he decided to try to tell me I had no clue what I was talking about when In my opinion it’s an insult to ask your customers for more money to provide health insurance. If you want to provide that for your employees by all means please do. But don’t expect me pay a premium just because you’re incapable of actually caring for your employees. After a few back and forth emails he became insulting and almost childlike. The food was decent, but expect to pay a premium for mostly just noodles. And you will also leave hungry. Go to Carmine’s, RPM Italian or the other 500 Italian places in the city and you’ll do much better.

Overall my experience at Daisies was okay. It was quite stuffy on the inside which led to a warm environment. The drink menu was very reasonably priced with an excellent wine list. The food was amazing. I had the tortellini and found it very well balanced. The GM walked around and intermingled with guests which stood out to me in a good way.  I think the only negative experience, outside of the environment, was the unprofessional staff. Not in a sense that they didn’t care about what they were doing, but everyone we came in contact with at our table definitely seemed as if it was their first or maybe second job in the service industry. One particular instance was when a waiter spilled a plate of our order onto the table next to us. I asked for a certain flavor profile of wine in one instance, and our waiter seemed kind of puzzled and unsure of his response. I do not know if it’s unfair of me to say this, but I expected a more experienced staff.  I will definitely come back for a glass of wine and a fantastic pasta dish, hopefully next time the staff is more prepared.
Excellent combination of flavors.  Skip the  fish fry and the vinegar soda. Everything else is worth trying. Cozy,  good place to impress your friends.
Brunch was amazing!! Try the polenta waffles with cherries🤗
Phenomenal food, but one issue was the restaurant was sweltering hot.  Made for a physically uncomfortable atmosphere when the room got crowded.  But great service and food.
Amazing pasta, pricey but worth it
Great brunch

We came in a group of 8 people and did the sharing menu. We were sat 20 minutes after our reservation. The inside is tight and stuffy. The windows don’t open in the front so it was hot.  The host and waitress were both very nice and helpful. Service was great. Bussers were extremely attentive.  Food was mediocre except for a couple dishes like the pappardelle and white fish. Everything was SO salty. The sharing menu offered plenty of food which was a plus. Drinks were reasonably priced for Chicago and had a great wine list.  I’m not sure we would chose to go back. It was just OK. Highlight for sure was the service.
The food was excellent. The service was exceptional. The waiter  was very friendly, patient with and attentive to our table. Great experience. Highly recommend.
Seasonal menu focused on Italian pastas

The food is exceptional and service great. Creative flavor combinations, all of which worked well together. We got a salad full of herbs that was really fresh and bright. A homemade gnocchi with a light cream sauce of morels that was AMAZING and a ravioli with peas, which was not my favorite, but perfectly al dente. Also the carrot appetizer is a must.

If you're debating coming here, debate no more, you have to try this place! Excellent food (like beyond excellent... Seriously), and excellent service (Jasmine rocks, so helpful). We had the mushrooms and cheese curds, gnocchi, and trout. Amazing flavors!
Very delicious

We made a reservation for Sunday Brunch at Daisies for a party of 8. They were so wonderful.  We had two children in our group and they seated us in the back room where the girls were able to read books and play without a problem. Our waiter was very knowledgeable about the wine list and patient in reviewing menu choices. The food was outstanding with extremely fresh ingredients.  The Bruschetta Scrambled Eggs with truffle oil was a fantastic dish. They were very accommodating to the girls who loved their pancakes. It was our son’s birthday and we brought cake.  They served us and were very happy to be part of our celebration.  Daisies is a favorite of our son and now we see why. A beautifully decorated location with incredible food, phenomenal service and great attention to detail with friendly and pleasant staff!
Lovely mother's day brunch. Thank you for having gluten free options and your homemade pasta was just delightful!
The food is really delicious, the staff was highly professional. Our server knew the menu well and was able to answer all our questions. Cute place! Definitely will go back.
Couldn't be more pleased! Had great food options and the bill was just right. Lovely people and great service. Thank you.
Amazing food and service. Best homemade pasta. Quality locally sourced vegetables. Great service.
The food not only looks great, its delicious!
The French onion dip and chips were a nice start.   You can't go wrong with the pastas!  We had a great server who helped piece our menu together too!  We will be returning!

So delish! Big bold pasta menu, every dish is totally unique and creative. Loved all the appetizers, we ordered almost all of them! I had the tortellini (pictured) and I loved the fried mushroom and cheese curd appetizer. Great place! 👍
A-maz-ing!  Chef Joe and his team provide an outstanding meal, between food, service and drinks.

I will give it 4 stars overall for the service, the caring of its employees (2% charge for providing them with healthcare), the welcome feel and the drinks menu. Also the fact that they cater for people with allergies is amazing!  On the other hand ... the food. I had the pappardelle selection. I found the dish very salty and the mushroomssightly undercooked. Additionally, the pasta was slightly undercooked.  About $125 for 2 people with 4 drinks and 2 main entrés.  Thanks however for making a guest feel at home!

Cannot speak highly enough of this restaurant. Warm, welcoming, and knowledgeable staff. And the kitchen backs it up with stellar food. Cocktails are on point, and wine selection is interesting and well curated. Thank you for a great night!
Great food and drinks.  Excellent service.

Just had our second experience at Daisies and we absolutely love this place. Service is always attentive and the menu is well-curated, from wine offerings to the thoughtful menu items using seasonality and local ingredients to their advantage. Just check out their Instagram if you want to see their hand-made pasta from its delicious beginnings. Very affordable too when you consider this level of dining. Both times we've split two pastas, two apps and a bottle of wine and hovered around the $150 mark with the appropriate tip included :)  We'll be back, but we'll wait until it's warmer to see what's changing on the menu.

Extremely small selection of beers. The food we did eat was good, but nothing unique or especially well done, and certainly not justifying the prices. Staff was solid. Just can't see any reason to justify returning or recommending when there are so many better options in such a tight area.
Try the pasta
Good food. Disappointingly overpriced and seems more like a hype though... for what they served.
Crowded venue; very cramped and tight, feeling. Staff was mediocre, at best.

Delicious cozy spot for brunch. Great service. Cute decor. Delicious food . Love the pasta dish. The pierogies are yum as is the potato latke (which comes out looking like it's a fully loaded pancake. Totally worth checking out.

What a fabulous dining experience! From walking us through the wine list to describing the various handmade pastas, the service was exceptional. We did the "Feed Me" option which included eight pre-selected dishes -- two appetizers, five pastas, and a dessert -- each of which was distinctive and delicious. My personal favorite was the Manti with butternut squash and smoked onion, though I would order any/all of the pasta offerings again in a heartbeat. What's more, they were very attentive to the fact that my husband is a pescatarian and were very mindful about making vegetarian substitutions, when able, and serving the bacon component of several pasta dishes on the side. All in all, I can't say enough good things about Daisies and will certainly be back!
Fun and delicious, but loud.
Delectable, fresh pasta with inventive, not far fetched, combinations of flavor.
Expensive, but excellent food and ambiance.

Wonderful service, and just great people! They add a 2% charge to offer health care for employees, how great is that? We would definitely go back to support an organization that treats their employees well and values offering benefits to their employees.  The food was delicious, the service was on point!!!  The only small drawback was that the a acoustics were bad but all other things make up for it. Highly recommend!!

Staged here and they hooked me up. Pasta is on the level, everything is on point. Michelin quality but without the frills. Variance for fermentation and every soul in the restuarant is focused on quality.
Cozy small plate place.

The food was tasty, but there wasn't much of it for the price. I got the tortellini, well specifically I got 12 of them, because they were so easy to count. :) I also thought the pork sausage was in the tortellini, but there were just three tiny bits of it mixed in. The tortellini were just lentils, which didn't justify the price at all. If you are a foodie who likes to take pictures of your food, it was nicely presented. But don't expect to leave full. We had some pizza after we left.
We enjoyed our food - especially the polenta waffles - but didn't live up the hype at all.
Intimate dining experience with a great staff that's actually knowledgeable about the food.

Delicious food and incredible staff. I was very impressed. We ordered a couple appetizers then each ordered a main dish, and shared.We had 2 pasta dishes, a pork  and a RICE KRISPIE crusted perch! Each dish was so fresh, creative and tasty.  We still has just enough room for delicious and boozy desserts.
Great pasta, really friendly and pleasant staff. Back patio is the way to go weather permitting.
INCREDIBLE. Went for the pasta, stayed for the flavorful tomato starter, great wine selection, delicious dessert, and attentive staff. One of the best dinners I have had in a while.
An innovative restaurant, focused on pastas with interesting unique sauces. Great service. Friendly staff all around my
Small plates but delicious food. Clean and well lit interiors. Pretty and enclosed outside seating space in the back. Good coffee but no espresso machine.

Good pasta, don't order the fried mushrooms.  Response: While visually appealing, the fried mushrooms we're void of any flavor, similar to eating rice cakes. This was unrepresentative of everything else I ate there.
Best pasta in town!!
Unique and delicious food.  Service was very attentive without being stifling.

This may be the best food I have eaten this year... Wow  Make sure to try the "Overpriced Tomato".... It is for sure Overpriced and worth every penny. The linguini was also beyond amazing and the drinks were delicious!  Highly recommended
Great

The food was good and the staff was friendly. The beet old fashioned was good as well, although there was very little beet taste. The price for the portions was far too high for my liking. The waiter suggested 5 plates between two people, and dessert, at $16-22  per plate.
Best pasta in the city hands down.

I love restaurants that allow the chef to shine and daisies encapsulates that. I appreciate how flexible they were in taking care of my girlfriend’s dietary restrictions but yet made the experience very memorable. Deceptively large space and a cute patio as well. Great dinner. Pastas are fresh and service is friendly.
One of the best meals I've had in Chicago, definitely in a long time, probably ever.
Lots of veggie options and great service!

Absolutely do not miss Daisies. Inventive menu that changes frequently with seasonal veggies. Almost everything available completely vegetarian. Dinner and brunch are both absolutely delicious. Attentive, fun, kind staff. Great vibe with outdoor patio avaialble. I give Daisies a whole Galaxy of stars.
Service was great, and food was unexpected and delicious!
Good food. Pricey limited yet creative brunch menu. Overall I liked but probably won't be going back for lunch. I'd like to see how their dinner fare fares.
Friendly staff and very delicious pasta! The portions are perfect and the pasta is not mushy!
Love this place. The staff is very welcoming. The food is amazing and they always have great wine recommendations! Highly recommend this place.

Small, unassuming and a pleasant surprise. Known for their pastas (agnolotti pictured, linguine with bacon and egg yolk were both 👍🏼) but really interesting starters (asparagus bruschetta with bone marrow and blue cheese, crispy portobello with egg and chicken gravy) and cocktails. Beet old fashioned and bourbon/wine sangria were refreshing. Server was very accommodating for dairy allergy. Will be back.
Well curated menu and friendly staff.
I love this place
Wonderful culinary experience. Food is delicious; staff is friendly and helpful. We will be going back...soon!
Love the flavors at this place, but I agree with the other reviewer that it would be great if there was a vegetarian dinner option with a protein and not just pasta.
Great wait staff, great food. The $1 oatmeal square is a great way way to finish a meal.
Great food and service!
Love this place! All the pastas are amazing. Salads are beyond fresh. Service is impeccable. Looking forward to coming back soon. Hoping the weathers gets good enough to dine al fresco there soon.

LOVED dinner last night! We had a sampling which included soft shell crabs, an intensely fresh green salad, four or five divine pastas and an exceptionally hip n unique beet old fashion. Everything we devoured because it tasted so great. What a cool place with perfectly executed food and no nonsense, kind and knowledgable service. Plus they have a hidden gem outdoor space for dining.

Friendly, classy little neighborhood restaurant with great food and one of the best wine lists in Logan Square. Big back patio. Delicious pasta, most (all?) of which can be requested as gluten-free. Emphasis on regional food, and even some Midwestern wines that are great finds.
Absolutely phenomenal.  Do not miss out on this hidden gem.

This is one of those local eateries that is perfect for a variety of occasions. Whether it's date night or a meal with a client, this is a great intimate, upscale restaurant. Be prepared to spend some good money for some delicious food. There's plenty of metered street parking in the area, but it's also accessible by the blue line.
Incredible pasta. Pillowy gnocchi, tender ravioli and perfectly al dente linguine.

🤗 Meal experienced: weekend brunch Ambience: relaxed, not too crowded Food: unique and well executed Service: friendly and well paced  Highlight dish: tarajin carbonara  The menu is very unique and not just your typical new American! Everything we got was worthwhile.
Small portions but the ambiance is so nice and the food is amazing
(Translated by Google) Amaaaaazing.  (Original) Amaaaaazing.
Great ambiance. Delicious and fresh dining. Nice bar and excellent service.
Been to Daisies quite a few times and it's always been stellar! Friendly service/bartender, local wine and the best pasta! If you haven't checked this place out yet what are you waiting for??
Ended up here for brunch and we were not disappointed! Excellent service and delectable foods! Super with our two yr old. We’ll be back
Nice place for brunch
Great food and wine.  The waiter was very knowledgeable and was able to help us pick a bottle of wine that worked perfectly with our dinner.

We had a reservation. Arrived on time. They walked our party of 4 to the back rooms. Whoops no table. We walked back up front and found out they gave our table to another party. Ended up waiting at the bar and sitting down about 10-15 minutes later. Gave us free chips and dip for waiting. The waitress was a bit snippy but it was pretty loud in there so that may have come off that way unintentionally. We ordered pasta for each of us. Pasta was good and fresh. I would come again but wasn't blown away. The apple herb salad we ordered for the table was fresh and crisp but no salad dressing to speak of so it was like eating an apple with herbs cut from the garden. It was supposed to have dressing so they ended up taking it back and not charging us. It was nice the manager didn't try and argue they just accommodated. We'd return to give it another shot.
Surprised at how good this place was. They obviously care a ton about creating good food.
Great food. Small space with no fluff - just amazing dishes. Save room for dessert.
My only regret about this place is not trying it sooner. Both dishes I had tonight were fantastic (squash salad and beet agnolotti) and I can't wait to come back and try more.
The best pasta I've ever had. I wish I could eat here every day. Amazing. A must eat at in Chicago.

They have an extremely seasonal menu, so any recommended dish is likely to be gone by the time you get there. The pastas are very diverse, no matter what you like there is likely something there you'll enjoy.
It's a cute place but I still want more out of it. Food is solid and staff is friendly. Huge potential there.
Love coming here with my wife
Best pasta I've found in Chicago. Fantastic service. Will be back!
the butternut squash salad was phenomenal!
Food and staff were amazing
Good plates. A bit on the expensive side. Some fun, creative cocktails. Definitely attracts a River North type crowd though.
From the great cocktails,  great service,  butternut salad and lamb stracci pasta dish! All excellent,  will definitely go back.

This is the best Italian food I've ever eaten. I want to move into Daisies, permanently. The lamb was to die for, the mixed drinks are lovely and the staff are the most relaxed, patient people. Despite a difficult table mate, they shone through the dinner to give us the best meal I had in 2017. Seriously, go here and your taste buds will thank you for days

Come here for the best hand made pasta. On your way to the bathroom, peek into the open kitchen to see chefs working their asses off to deliver incredible flavor and inventive ingredient combinations. Atmosphere is busy but talkable. Half our party were vegetarian and we didn't even miss the meat since the flavors were so bangin. Go here now.
Quickly becoming one of my favorite dinner options. Delicious house made pasta and  local vegetables. A very interesting wine list adds to the experience.
Delicious pastas and the roasted carrot app was incredible
The pasta is outta this world.

Fantastic food, fantastic service. A real find. The pasta is the star, but the appetizers are terrific. We got 5 apps and 5 entrees for 5 people and didn't take anything home. A bit off the beaten track for sure, but that's a good thing if you're driving. Reservations are definitely a good idea.
I was a little underwhelmed, given how much hype this place has

Hands-down and without a doubt the best pasta I've ever had in my life. I have reviewed numerous pasta joints throughout the years but this has far and away been the best. The cocktails were fantastic, unique and flavorful. I could've eaten 4 servings of the zucchini appetizer alone! Oh but that pasta! My companion and I ended up ordering 3 plates of pasta because it was so delicious. The portion sizes are on the smaller side, it's not a heaping mound of mushy garbage like you get at Olive Garden. Definitely going back soon! Please go and enjoy these pasta masters, you won't be disappointed.
The Tagliatelle was one of the best!
A bit cramped but the food was very delicious and the service was fantastic and accommodating.
Food was amazing and waiters/staff were SO friendly and helpful. They have a few rotating dishes which is nice.

When I am going out to dinner I am looking for something different that I can't just make at home. Daisies is the perfect restaurant for exactly this. The food is delicious and you leave without feeling weighed down by a lot of butter or salt.
Truly unique and delicious pasta dishes. The wine list and beet old fashioned are also worth trying. The kitchen sent us two complimentary pasta dishes for whatever reason, the service is incredible!

Great food! Very innovative combination of tasty and fresh ingredients. inconsistent size of portions. We had the fried mushrooms as appetizer, very interesting. I had the pierogi, excellent decent size. My husband had the agnolotti, execellent as well but the size of a tapas (less than 10). Good kalua cake and cocktails.

Daisies is why Chicago is a premiere Food City!  We came as a party of 4, and every bite we enjoyed tasted fresh, high quality, and exciting.  While we truly liked everything, the pastas here steak the show.  The ones we ordered rivaled dishes I've enjoyed at Michelin-Star'd restaurants, especially the Pierogi, which were perfectly balanced pillows of perfection.  The dining room is cozy and welcoming, much like the staff and the menu; Chef/Owner Joe Frillman has built a Midwest pasta temple, that demands repeat visits.
Fantastic white fish dish and pastas. The service was great.
Tasty pasta, but given the focus on pasta and vegetables, it would be really nice if their vegetarian options had some protein.
Excellent food and drinks, nice patio out back too!

I've now dined multiple times and can honestly say the food here is excellent. Fresh and locally sourced, with a unique touch on classic and down to earth dishes. Some of the favorite starters: Carrot Rillettes (fresh fresh fraîche), Onion Dip (simple and addicting), Burrata (anywhere can serve burrata, but this dish sets itself apart).  For main courses, you cannot go wrong. Seriously. I've had everything and not a single disappointment, but some highlights include: Tagliatelle (yes, add black truffle if you can), Agnolotti (such an interesting and delicious mix with beets), and the fish (eat the skin, I know that may sound weird, but the way it's prepared makes the skin arguably the most flavorful part).  Overall, highly recommend you try before this place starts to circulate and books up. Cheers!
Just went last night, the food was delicious and the service spectacular!  The chips and dip were awesome, but my fav was the burrata, so delicate and soooo tasty.   Way to go Joe Frillman!
Great experience here, excellent drinks, and delicious, beautifully presented, inventive food. Can't wait to go back (the tortellini was incredible)
VG very good. The Kahlua cake was Mary Barry good XD :p
would recommend
